Who said I was mad?

91
00:08:12,860 --> 00:08:16,210
Wait... but this facial expression shows...

92
00:08:16,210 --> 00:08:19,100
You're definitely flustered.

93
00:08:20,090 --> 00:08:22,790
- Me?
- Yes.

94
00:08:22,790 --> 00:08:24,620
No, it's not.

95
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:28,970
Don't pull a face.

96
00:08:29,570 --> 00:08:34,150
Your prophecy changed. But because 
of that, we saved the child.

97
00:08:36,260 --> 00:08:41,560
That's true but... Because I don't
know what changed the prophecy,

98
00:08:43,100 --> 00:08:45,810
I feel nervous.

99
00:08:45,810 --> 00:08:51,960
It could be a miracle. They say that if you want 
something desperately enough, it can come true.

100
00:08:52,690 --> 00:08:55,480
It's not that I haven't 
thought of that already.

101
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:57,900
The moment they said Mi Jin was alive,

102
00:08:57,900 --> 00:09:01,570
I thought, "Wow, this is really a miracle."

103
00:09:01,570 --> 00:09:03,240
But?

104
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:08,490
Everyone who has believed my 
prophecies were desperate

105
00:09:08,490 --> 00:09:11,790
and they all wanted to change fate.

106
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:17,380
Some people spent several billion won;

107
00:09:17,380 --> 00:09:21,140
and among them, some tried to do 
something hard for several dozen years.

108
00:09:21,140 --> 00:09:25,000
But it doesn't make sense that 
this is the one time a miracle happens.

109
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:31,930
Then... I must have the ability 
to change the fate of death.

110
00:09:38,810 --> 00:09:41,000
I was joking...

111
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:44,430
Over there!

112
00:09:44,430 --> 00:09:46,450
Take pictures!

113
00:09:46,450 --> 00:09:49,270
Let's go. I'll take you home.

114
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:27,890
Honey, I think something happened to Mi Jin.

115
00:10:30,260 --> 00:10:32,900
Honey, please pick up your phone. Please!

116
00:10:32,900 --> 00:10:35,440
What if our Mi Jin dies?

117
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:38,890
YBS is already doing breaking news, 
yet we don't have the victim's identity?

118
00:10:38,890 --> 00:10:42,700
That's my daughter! Mi Jin! Mom is here!

119
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:46,970
- Mi Jin!
- Ma'am, you cannot go in there.

120
00:10:46,970 --> 00:10:49,590
Mi Jin!
[Rescue of the Buried Victim Ongoing, Mother On Site.]

121
00:11:30,410 --> 00:11:32,500
I'm sorry...

122
00:11:33,750 --> 00:11:35,440
I'm sorry.

123
00:11:55,330 --> 00:11:58,150
- Please have some coffee.
- Oh, thank you.

124
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:07,870
- Is there anyone you suspect? 
- Have you received any threats recently?

125
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:12,250
No. Not at all.

126
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:19,320
Thank you so much for saving my child.

127
00:12:19,320 --> 00:12:22,680
I know it, because I wrote the 
articles about Jo Pil Doo's case,

128
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:26,500
how much of a miracle it 
was that she was rescued.

129
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:32,510
Then... that seventh victim was 
rescued through a miracle...

130
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:37,340
You must remember how she
was killed at the hospital.

131
00:12:37,920 --> 00:12:39,500
Section Chief.

132
00:12:39,500 --> 00:12:42,030
I'm just saying that we 
should all be careful.

133
00:12:42,030 --> 00:12:45,810
That kind of thing can't happen again.

134
00:12:47,330 --> 00:12:51,120
I increased the hospital 
security with maximum manpower.

135
00:12:51,980 --> 00:12:55,380
And instead of thanking me,

136
00:12:55,380 --> 00:12:58,450
you should thank Detective 
Seo Joon Yeong,

137
00:12:58,450 --> 00:13:01,030
whom you bothered so much because of 
being crazy about your scoop 20 years ago.

138
00:13:01,570 --> 00:13:04,180
That kid saved your daughter.

139
00:13:18,910 --> 00:13:22,090
Reporters are really something.

140
00:13:22,090 --> 00:13:23,980
Why?

141
00:13:23,980 --> 00:13:28,500
The stuff that you found out with lots of effort...  
They knew it right away and ran down immediately.

142
00:13:28,500 --> 00:13:34,160
I know, right? We should've caught 
Jo Pil Doo immediately like that.

143
00:13:35,150 --> 00:13:37,070
Jo Pil Doo?

144
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:44,920
What is this?

145
00:13:44,920 --> 00:13:46,640
What do you mean?

146
00:13:49,380 --> 00:13:53,070
You don't know serial killer Jo Pil Doo?

147
00:13:53,070 --> 00:13:55,100
Should I know him?

148
00:13:57,270 --> 00:13:59,090
Of course!

149
00:13:59,090 --> 00:14:02,310
You don't watch TV, 
the news, or newspapers?

150
00:14:02,310 --> 00:14:04,530
- No.
- Whoa.

151
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:18,860
What's going on?

152
00:14:18,860 --> 00:14:21,610
Okay! At this time, 
reporters cannot come in,

153
00:14:21,610 --> 00:14:24,280
So please go back home. What about the 
victim's condition? Just tell us her condition!

154
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:27,840
- There is nothing I can tell you.
- That's why we're asking you to find out!

155
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:30,230
- Because we don't know enough yet—
- It's Section Chief Nam!

156
00:14:30,230 --> 00:14:32,850
- Section Chief!  
- Section Chief! Please here!

157
00:14:32,850 --> 00:14:36,210
Section Chief! Please! 
Just tell us one thing!

158
00:14:36,210 --> 00:14:40,090
Is this case connected to 
the past Jo Pil Doo case?

159
00:14:50,210 --> 00:14:54,560
Then... that seventh victim 
was rescued through a miracle...

160
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:58,330
you must remember how she 
was killed at the hospital.

161
00:15:07,690 --> 00:15:09,840
Yes, Captain!

162
00:15:09,840 --> 00:15:12,450
Yes, the victim's condition took a 
favorable turn, so 30 minutes ago

163
00:15:12,450 --> 00:15:14,540
she was moved to a regular hospital room.

164
00:15:14,540 --> 00:15:21,010
Because there were no records of a gynecologist
visiting, it seems that there wasn't any sexual abuse.

165
00:15:21,010 --> 00:15:23,360
What? Photos?

166
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:27,420
Yes, understood! Yes!

167
00:15:36,780 --> 00:15:39,020
Please don't take any photos.

168
00:15:40,970 --> 00:15:41,880
What is this, right now?

169
00:15:41,880 --> 00:15:47,550
Oh, Sir, hello. I'm Reporter Lee Joon Hui from 
Hana Daily. Would it be possible to have an interview?

170
00:16:15,080 --> 00:16:16,940
Dad?

171
00:16:24,350 --> 00:16:28,190
- You should've caught him. 
- You should've stopped him!

172
00:16:28,190 --> 00:16:31,050
If you had done your job properly, 
why would my daughter have died?

173
00:16:31,050 --> 00:16:35,200
How the hell did that bastard know 
which hospital room my daughter stayed in?

174
00:16:35,200 --> 00:16:39,300
- Bring her back. Bring her back!
- Please let go, so we can talk.

175
00:16:39,300 --> 00:16:43,420
Wait... But how did that criminal 
know where the victims was located?

176
00:16:43,420 --> 00:16:45,090
Did it leak from an insider?

177
00:16:45,090 --> 00:16:48,430
Wait, how did he know 
exactly which hospital room?

178
00:16:48,430 --> 00:16:52,970
- Does that make any sense?
- That's what I'm saying!

179
00:16:52,970 --> 00:16:58,200
You said you would catch him! You said 
you would save my kid! Calm down please.

180
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:02,950
You said you would catch him!

181
00:17:02,950 --> 00:17:07,890
You said you would save my kid!

182
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:22,220
[307. Lee Mi Jin]

183
00:17:37,230 --> 00:17:40,840
Wait... So you don't watch TV at all?

184
00:17:43,430 --> 00:17:45,030
No.

185
00:17:46,400 --> 00:17:51,000
It must be harder than I thought, 
to live with that ability.

186
00:17:52,990 --> 00:17:57,590
If you don't watch TV, you probably 
have never seen a movie, either.

187
00:17:57,590 --> 00:18:00,560
Yeah, if you're watching 
a melodramatic movie

188
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:04,670
and if you can see the main character's death, 
your mood will be ruined right away.

189
00:18:04,670 --> 00:18:07,870
Then, have you never 
been to a movie theater?

190
00:18:07,870 --> 00:18:13,370
Wow, I haven't been because I'm busy. But not 
going because you can't is totally different.

191
00:18:13,370 --> 00:18:17,300
Then, what do you do when you're alone? 
What do you do for fun?

192
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:23,030
I'm sure you can't go to 
places with a lot of people.

193
00:18:23,030 --> 00:18:25,160
Is there anywhere you like?

194
00:18:30,490 --> 00:18:35,540
Is it because I can't see her death?

195
00:18:37,260 --> 00:18:39,630
Her facial expressions

196
00:18:40,870 --> 00:18:45,860
are endearing for the first time.

197
00:18:49,580 --> 00:18:52,520
Looking at someone,

198
00:18:52,520 --> 00:18:55,620
is it this kind of feeling?

199
00:18:59,530 --> 00:19:05,940
But why do you keep staring at me like that? 
Is there something on my face?

200
00:19:07,910 --> 00:19:10,400
No. Nothing's on your face.

201
00:19:11,140 --> 00:19:13,740
Look forward and drive comfortably.

202
00:19:37,220 --> 00:19:38,830
You're not leaving?

203
00:19:44,360 --> 00:19:46,640
Thank you for today.

204
00:19:49,420 --> 00:19:50,970
I'm glad I could be helpful.

205
00:19:50,970 --> 00:19:54,760
Right? It was good that 
I forced you to help, right?

206
00:19:58,360 --> 00:20:03,710
But ... earlier, when you 
said you felt nervous,

207
00:20:03,710 --> 00:20:08,500
you said that you thought there was a 
reason that her death changed. Right?

208
00:20:09,170 --> 00:20:13,780
Do you want to figure 
out that reason together?

209
00:20:15,220 --> 00:20:21,080
You may be able to find out the reason if you 
deal with the murder cases like Mi Jin's case.

210
00:20:23,480 --> 00:20:27,210
I know we're going to be busy 
trying to solve this case, but

211
00:20:27,210 --> 00:20:31,580
would you... want to 
work together sometime?

212
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:40,640
I'll think about it.

213
00:20:42,460 --> 00:20:44,080
You should go.

214
00:20:44,080 --> 00:20:45,830
All right.

215
00:20:46,770 --> 00:20:48,610
Then, goodnight.

216
00:21:27,900 --> 00:21:31,980
My prophecies have never changed.

217
00:21:31,980 --> 00:21:35,380
We can change that prophecy.

218
00:21:35,380 --> 00:21:37,870
It's unfortunate but you should head back.

219
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:42,140
I will show you that we can change it.

220
00:21:42,140 --> 00:21:44,510
She's breathing. She's alive!

221
00:21:44,510 --> 00:21:48,420
You said that you thought there was a 
reason that her death changed, right?

222
00:21:48,420 --> 00:21:53,000
Do you want to figure 
out that reason together?

223
00:22:04,730 --> 00:22:05,870
Starting now,

224
00:22:05,870 --> 00:22:11,260
we will begin the briefing 
on the case of last night,

225
00:22:11,260 --> 00:22:12,760
that a female high school student was kidnapped and 
attempted to be murdered in the Bongrae neighborhood.

226
00:22:12,760 --> 00:22:17,250
On the night of the 15th around 
8:00 p.m., the team on duty

227
00:22:17,250 --> 00:22:18,800
got a call from the victim—

228
00:22:18,800 --> 00:22:22,640
The section chief will have to go 
to the Blue House to report this.

229
00:22:22,640 --> 00:22:27,080
We didn't even catch the culprit. I don't 
know which one is priority or posteriority.

230
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:29,570
In any case, the fact that 
Mi Jin survived is a miracle.

231
00:22:29,570 --> 00:22:31,890
We recognized the seriousness of the 
crime and tried to locate the buried victim...

232
00:22:31,890 --> 00:22:34,220
Let's go. I'm hungry. Let's go and eat.

233
00:22:34,220 --> 00:22:35,870
Yes.

234
00:22:52,180 --> 00:22:57,430
You've grown up so much, 
I barely recognize you.

235
00:22:57,430 --> 00:23:01,610
If someone else heard this, 
they'd think we were very close.

236
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:05,030
Right.

237
00:23:06,870 --> 00:23:09,060
I don't know how 
to thank you enough...

238
00:23:09,060 --> 00:23:11,760
I just did my job.

239
00:23:11,760 --> 00:23:17,560
I don't think you came here just 
to say that. Let's get to the point.

240
00:23:20,410 --> 00:23:22,250
Hello.

241
00:23:30,710 --> 00:23:33,400
I dug through newspaper after newspaper.

242
00:23:33,400 --> 00:23:37,650
But the picture that showed the hospital 
room number was only in my article.

243
00:23:37,650 --> 00:23:42,120
Right after this article went out, 
the child died the next day.

244
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:47,000
I knew right away that Jo Pil Doo 
went to the child after seeing my article.

245
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:53,050
So I wanted to hide it until the end...

246
00:23:53,050 --> 00:23:55,340
But that child's dad must've seen my article.

247
00:23:55,340 --> 00:24:00,480
I'm sure he couldn't forgive me since his daughter, 
who'd been rescued with a lot of effort, died because of me.

248
00:24:04,470 --> 00:24:09,980
Jo Pil Doo could've seen the hospital 
room number after seeing this article.

249
00:24:09,980 --> 00:24:16,200
But for the girl's father to take 
revenge on you for this article is a bit...

250
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:19,220
If he'd seen the picture, 
the victim's father

251
00:24:19,220 --> 00:24:23,130
would've probably been more concerned about his 
daughter's face than the hospital room number.

252
00:24:24,990 --> 00:24:27,970
This is the last picture of 
his daughter before her death.

253
00:24:27,970 --> 00:24:32,730
And the possibility of him 
seeing this article is unlikely.

254
00:24:32,730 --> 00:24:35,490
Every day, articles about 
his daughter's death appeared.

255
00:24:35,490 --> 00:24:39,040
And on top of that, at the hospital,
even though her parents were a few meters away,

256
00:24:39,040 --> 00:24:43,650
she was killed.  Those kinds of 
articles appeared almost every day.

257
00:24:43,650 --> 00:24:47,380
Would he be able to read the newspapers?

258
00:24:49,870 --> 00:24:54,120
He would've read them if he hadn't 
known how his daughter had died.

259
00:24:56,030 --> 00:24:58,870
Because I did that.

260
00:24:58,870 --> 00:25:03,960
I saw my father's body through 
an article that you put out.

261
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:12,260
A photo of width: 20 cm, height: 15 cm.

262
00:25:12,260 --> 00:25:15,950
I saw my father's body 
in that small photo,

263
00:25:15,950 --> 00:25:18,670
but I couldn't believe it.

264
00:25:18,670 --> 00:25:23,580
There were 9 fractures in his ribs.

265
00:25:23,580 --> 00:25:26,750
Both ankles and the pelvis

266
00:25:26,750 --> 00:25:28,800
were ruptured beyond recognition...

267
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:31,930
The rest of the six victims' buried 
locations were not revealed yet. Stop it.

268
00:25:31,930 --> 00:25:35,020
Then the date of Jo Pil Doo's on-the-spot 
investigation isn't scheduled yet?

269
00:25:35,020 --> 00:25:36,840
Just tell me, please!

270
00:25:36,840 --> 00:25:39,380
Stop it!

271
00:25:39,380 --> 00:25:42,390
Detective Nam, I'm a reporter.

272
00:25:42,390 --> 00:25:45,030
I'm doing this for the people's right to know—

273
00:25:45,030 --> 00:25:46,870
Geez!! This bastard.

274
00:25:46,870 --> 00:25:50,720
That you searched the body of a cop who died while chasing after 
a culprit and put it on the news, is for the people's right to know?

275
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:53,110
What in the world is a right 
to know that you mentioned?

276
00:25:53,110 --> 00:25:55,770
You're too much!

277
00:25:55,770 --> 00:25:58,420
Seo Joon Yeong is here...

278
00:26:01,090 --> 00:26:03,010
Joon Yeong!

279
00:26:08,950 --> 00:26:16,030
The article said there were nine fractures 
in his ribs. And eyes, nose, lips, and ears,

280
00:26:16,030 --> 00:26:19,690
even his burst head, broken legs,

281
00:26:19,690 --> 00:26:23,490
and blood all over his 
body were documented.

282
00:26:24,340 --> 00:26:28,030
But after I became a 
police officer, I found out.

283
00:26:28,030 --> 00:26:32,530
It wasn't 9. But 13 fractures.

284
00:26:34,210 --> 00:26:35,470
I'm sorry.  Back then, I—

285
00:26:35,470 --> 00:26:38,280
You must've gone crazy 
about trying to get scoops.

286
00:26:40,740 --> 00:26:43,340
I understand your belief.

287
00:26:44,170 --> 00:26:50,130
But why would the victim's father 
take his revenge after 20 years?

288
00:26:53,790 --> 00:26:56,960
To give me the same kind of pain.

289
00:26:58,830 --> 00:27:04,960
Back then that girl was kidnapped on the way 
home after buying a birthday cake, like my Mi Jin.

290
00:27:04,960 --> 00:27:09,050
And on that day, it was that 
girl's mother's birthday as well.

291
00:27:13,900 --> 00:27:17,810
The culprit is the 
seventh victim's father,

292
00:27:17,810 --> 00:27:19,800
Hong Jeong Ho.
